  <div class="section">
    <h2>6. AI Processing and Third-Party APIs</h2>
    <p>Polynote uses third-party AI services to enhance your experience:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>OpenAI Whisper: On-device speech-to-text transcription (no data sent to servers)</li>
      <li>OpenAI GPT-4o-mini: Cloud-based AI for generating study materials from transcript text</li>
      <li>Cloudflare Workers: Secure backend proxy for API requests</li>
    </ul>
    <p>When you use AI study materials features, your transcript text is sent to OpenAI via our backend proxy. Audio files are never uploaded. Study materials are generated once and cached locally. You can configure your own OpenAI API key or disable AI features in Settings. Use of OpenAI services is subject to OpenAI's Terms of Use and Privacy Policy.</p>
  </div>

